cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ITU and Linguistics: A Single-Axiom View of Phonology, Syntax, Semantics, Pragmatics, Language Acquisition, Sociolinguistics, Language Change, Endangered Languages, NLP, and Large Language Models — Pass-1 Extension Paper #3, Block C 1/6 OPENING"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Terada
    given-names: Munehiro
    affiliation: Roboken
    email: munehiro.terada@roboken2.com
abstract: >
  We apply the Information-Theoretic Unification (ITU) framework
  (Terada 2026, concept DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20109209; Tier 0 v3.0 at
  10.5281/zenodo.20200156) to linguistics. Tier 1 paper #33, the
  third paper of Pass-1 extension, OPENING Block C (social/humanities/
  arts) after Block A 10/10 + Block B 6/6 COMPLETE. Introduces K_lang
  across 8 sub-states (K_lang_phonology, K_lang_syntax, K_lang_semantics,
  K_lang_pragmatics, K_lang_acquisition, K_lang_socio,
  K_lang_computational, K_lang_universal). ITU axiom delta S = delta <K>
  verified to machine precision in 11+ linguistic contexts. 33-vertex
  ITU polytope with #33 Linguistics reaching new max degree 32.
  Key results: World languages 7,164 (Ethnologue 2024); Maddieson 1984
  avg 31 phonemes/lang, range 11 (Rotokas PNG) to 141 (!Xoo Khoisan);
  Greenberg 1963 SOV 41% + SVO 35% = 76%; Chomsky revolution 1957-2024
  (Syntactic Structures -> Standard Theory -> Principles and Parameters
  -> Minimalist Program -> Merge); Pirahã recursion controversy
  (Everett 2005); Lenneberg 1967 critical period 0-13 years; Werker-Tees
  1984 phonemic narrowing 6-12 months; Berlin-Kay 1969 color hierarchy
  7 stages; Frege 1892 Sinn vs Bedeutung; Montague 1970 lambda-calculus
  compositional semantics; Grice 1975 4 maxims; Searle 1969 5 speech
  acts; WordNet 117,000+ synsets; FrameNet 1,200+ frames; Bialystok
  bilingual dementia delay 4.7 years (Mendis 2020); Indo-European
  Steppe Hypothesis 5,500 BP (Gray-Atkinson 2003, ancient DNA);
  Endangered 3,000+ languages, 230+ extinct since 1950; Vaswani 2017
  Transformer; BERT/GPT-1 2018; GPT-3 175B 2020; ChatGPT 2022 1M users
  in 5 days; GPT-4o MMLU 88.7% (2024); Llama 3.1 405B open (2024);
  Chinchilla N ~= 20D scaling; Shannon English 1.0-1.5 bits/char;
  Piantadosi 2023 "Modern language models refute Chomsky's approach".
  Ten falsifiable predictions (P_avg = 0.780 - Pass-1 + extension
  highest, Strong/Medium/Weak = 7/3/0) including LLM 7000+ language
  translation 2028 (P=0.80), AI 100+ endangered langs documented 2028
  (P=0.85), LLM acquires UG emergently 2027 (P=0.75), AI L2 instruction
  50% acceleration 2028 (P=0.85), Embodied LLM body-grounded 2028
  (P=0.80), GPT-5/Claude 4 partial AGI 2026 (P=0.75), AI full Turing
  test passed 2027 (P=0.85), AI discovers new conceptual metaphor 2028
  (P=0.80). Block C OPENS 1/6 (social/humanities/arts). Remaining
  Block C: #34 Music/Arts, #35 Law, #36 Education, #37 History,
  #38 Anthropology. Pass-1 interpretive synthesis.
keywords:
